19}}</ref>\n* 2003 - [[Behrouz Daresh]], [[Hossein KhoroJerdi]], and [[Ahmad Nadalian]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kayhanlife.com/culture/art/iran-venice-biennale-visit-iranian-pavilion/|title=Iran at the Venice Biennial (Part I) &#124; KAYHAN LIFE|first=Kayhan|last=Life|accessdate=June 3, 2019}}</ref>\n* 2017 - [[Bizhan Bassiri]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kayhanlife.com/culture/art/iran-at-the-venice-biennale-a-visit-to-the-iranian-pavilion/|title=Iran at the Venice Biennale: A Visit to the Iranian Pavilion &#124; KAYHAN LIFE|first=Natasha|last=Phillips|accessdate=June 3, 2019}}</ref>\n* 2019 - [[Samira Alikhanza]], [[Ali Mir-Azimi]], and [[Reza  Lavasani]]  <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ifpnews.com/exclusive/irans-pavilion-opens-in-venice-biennial-arte-2019/|title=Iran\u2019s Pavilion Opens in Venice Biennial Arte 2019|first=IFP Editorial|last=Staff|date=May 11, 2019|website=IFP News - Iran Front Page|accessdate=June 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Iraq===\nIn 2011, Iraq returned to the Biennale for the first time after a 35-year absence. The title of the Iraq Pavilion was \"Acqua Ferita\" (translated as \"Wounded Water\"). Six Iraqi artists from two generations interpreted the theme of water in their works, which made up the exhibition. \n* 2011 \u2014 Adel Abidin, Halim Al Karim, Ahmed Alsoudani, Ali Assaf, Azad Nanakeli, Walid Siti\n* 2013 \u2014 'Welcome to Iraq', curated by [[Jonathan Watkins]], commissioned by [[Ruya Foundation]]. Artists: Abdul Raheem Yassir (b. 1951), Akeel Khreef (b. 1979), Ali Samiaa (b. 1980), Bassim Al-Shaker (b. 1986), Cheeman Ismaeel (b. 1966), Furat al Jamil (b. 1965), Hareth Alhomaam (b. 1987), Jamal Penjweny (b. 1981), Kadhim Nwir (b. 1967), Yaseen Wami (b. 1973), Hashim Taeeh.<ref>Ruya Foundation, ''Announcement'', March 21, 2013 [https://ruyafoundation.org/en/2013/03/announcement-of-artists-names/]</ref>\n* 2015 \u2014 'Invisible Beauty', curated by Philippe Van Cauteren, commissioned by [[Ruya Foundation]]. Artists:  [[Latif_al-Ani|Latif Al Ani]], Akam Shex Hadi, Rabab Ghazoul, Salam Atta Sabri and Haider Jabbar.<ref>Ruya Foundation, Invisible Beauty the Iraq Pavilion at the 56th Venice Biennale, April 1, 2016 [https://ruyafoundation.org/en/project/invisible-beauty-2/]</ref>\n* 2017 \u2014 'Archaic', curated by Tamara Chalabi and Paolo Colombo, commissioned by [[Ruya Foundation]]. Artists: Sherko Abbas, [[Sadik Kwaish Alfraji]], [[Francis Al\u00ffs]], Ali Arkady, Luary Fadhil, [[Shakir Hassan Al Said]], Nadine Hattom, [[Jawad Saleem]], Sakar Sleman<ref>Chalabi, T., ''Archaic: The Pavilion of Iraq : 57th International Art Exhibition La Biennale Di Venezia'', Mousse Publishing, 2017</ref><ref>Ruya Foundation, ''Archaic the Iraq Pavilion at the 57th Venice Biennale'', March 10, 2017 [https://ruyafoundation.org/en/project/venice-biennale-2017/]</ref>\n* 2019 \u2014 'Fatherland: Serwan Baran', curated by Tamara Chalabi and Paolo Colombo, commissioned by [[Ruya Foundation]]. Artist: Serwan Baran (b. 1968). <ref>Alex Greenberger (February 22, 2019), [http://www.artnews.com/2019/02/22/serwan-baran-will-represent-iraq-2019-venice-biennale/ Serwan Baran Will Represent Iraq at the 2019 Venice Biennale] ''[[ARTnews]]''.</ref><ref>Ruya Foundation, ''Fatherland: Serwan Baran the Iraq Pavilion at the 58th Venice Biennale'', April 1, 2019 [https://ruyafoundation.org/en/project/fatherland/]</ref>\n\n===Ireland===\nList of exhibitors in the Irish Pavilion:\n* 1950 \u2014 [[Norah McGuinness]], [[Nano Reid]]\n* 1956 \u2014 [[Louis le Brocquy]], Hilary Heron\n* 1960 \u2014 Patrick Scott\n* 1993 \u2014 Dorothy Cross, Willie Doherty\n* 1995 \u2014 [[Kathy Prendergast]]<ref>[[Michael Kimmelman]] (July 9, 1995), [https://www.nytimes.com/1995/07/09/arts/art-view-venice-biennale-startling-songs-of-the-body.html Venice Biennale: Startling Songs Of the Body...] ''[[New York Times]]''.</ref>\n* 1997 \u2014 [[Jaki Irvine]], Alastair MacLennan<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* 1999 \u2014 Anne Tallentire\n* 2001 \u2014 Siobhan Hapaska, Grace Weir\n* 2003 \u2014 [[Katie Holten]] (Commissioner: Valerie Connor)\n* 2005 \u2014 Stephen Brandes, Mark Garry, Ronan McCrea, [[Isabel Nolan]], Sarah Pierce, Walker and Walker (Commissioner: Sarah Glennie)\n* 2007 \u2014 [[Gerard Byrne (artist, born 1969)|Gerard Byrne]] (Commissioner: Mike Fitzpatrick)\n* 2009 \u2014 Sarah Browne, Gareth Kennedy, Kennedy Browne\n* 2011 \u2014 [[Corban Walker]] (Commissioner: Emily-Jane Kirwan)\n* 2013 \u2014 [[Richard Mosse]] (Commissioner: Anna O'Sullivan)\n* 2015 \u2014 Sean Lynch, [[The Rubberbandits]] (Commissioner: Mike Fitzpatrick; curator: Woodrow Kernohan)<ref>Aidan Dunne (January 12, 2015), [http://www.irishtimes.com/culture/art-and-design/visual-art/the-inventive-and-industrious-sean-lynch-is-a-good-fit-for-venice-biennale-1.2063091 The inventive and industrious Sean Lynch is a good fit for Venice Biennale] ''[[The Irish Times]]''.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.limerickleader.ie/what-s-on/arts-entertainment/visual-arts/the-rubberbandits-to-perform-at-the-venice-biennale-1-6726155|title=The Rubberbandits to perform at the Venice Biennale|publisher=}}</ref>\n* 2017 \u2014 Jesse Jones, [[Olwen Fou\u00e9r\u00e9]] (Curator: Tessa Giblin)\n* 2019 \u2014 [[Eva Rothschild]] (Curator: Mary Cremin)\n\n===Italy===\n\"Palazzo Pro Arte\": Enrico Trevisanato, fa\u00e7ade by Marius De Maria and Bartholomeo Bezzi, 1895; new fa\u00e7ade by Guido Cirilli, 1914; \"Padiglione Italia\", present fa\u00e7ade by Duilio Torres, 1932. The pavilion has a sculpture garden by [[Carlo Scarpa]], 1952 and the \"Auditorium Pastor\" by Valeriano Pastor, 1977.<ref name=\"Martino\"/>\n\nPartial list of exhibitors at the Italian Pavilion:\n\n* 1895 \u2014 [[Giuseppe Ferrari (painter)|Giuseppe Ferrari]]\n* 1905 \u2014 Giuseppe Ferrari\n* 1912 \u2014 [[Aldo Carpi]]\n* 1922 \u2014 Giuseppe Ferrari (posthumus)\n* 1934 \u2014 [[Aldo Carpi]], [[Carlo Martini]]\n* 1936 \u2014 Aldo Carpi, Carlo Martini, [[Quinto Martini (artist)|Quinto Martini]]\n* 1942 \u2014 Aldo Carpi, [[Trento Longaretti]]\n* 1948 \u2014 Aldo Carpi, Trento Longaretti, Carlo Martini\n* 1950 \u2014 Aldo Carpi, Trento Longaretti, Carlo Martini\n* 1966 \u2014 [[Ferruccio Bortoluzzi]], Trento Longaretti\n* 1968 \u2014 [[Valerio Adami]], [[Rodolfo Aric\u00f2]], Gianni Bertini, [[Arturo Bonfanti]], [[Gianni Colombo]], Mario Deluigi, Gianfranco Ferroni, Luciano Gaspari,&nbsp; Lorenzo Guerrini, Giovanni Korompay, [[Leoncillo Leonardi]], Carlo Mattioli, Livio Marzot, Mirko, [[Marcello Morandini]], [[Mario Nigro]], Gino Morandis, [[Pino Pascali]], Gastone Novelli, Achille Perilli, [[Michelangelo Pistoletto]], Tancredi, Guido Strazza, Giacomo Porzano<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Stefano|first=Chiara Di|title=Una Pagina Dimenticata - Analisi delle Tensioni Artistiche e Sociali alla Biennale Veneziana del 1968|url=https://www.academia.edu/7438933/Una_Pagina_Dimenticata_-_Analisi_delle_Tensioni_Artistiche_e_Sociali_alla_Biennale_Veneziana_del_1968|language=en}}</ref>\n\n* 1984 \u2014 [[Roberto Barni]], [[Alberto Burri]], [[Enrico Castellani]], [[Mario Ceroli]], [[Sandro Chia]], [[Giorgio De Chirico]], [[Luciano Fabro]], Tano Festa, Carlo Maria Mariani, Gino Marotta, Titina Maselli, [[Luigi Ontani]], [[Giulio Paolini]], Claudio Parmiggiani, [[Vettor Pisani]], [[Michelangelo Pistoletto]], [[Gi\u00f2 Pomodoro]], [[Mario Schifano]], Toti Scialoja, Massimo Scolari, Giuseppe Uncini, Luigi Nono (Curator: Maurizio Calvesi)\n* 1986 \u2014 [[Getulio Alviani]], [[Giovanni Anselmo]], Marco Bagnoli, [[Toni Benetton]], [[Alighiero Boetti]], Paolo Borghi, Francesco Borromini, Nicola Carrino, Claudio Costa, Sergio Dangelo, [[Giorgio De Chirico]], [[Luciano Fabro]], Piero Fogliati, [[Lucio Fontana]], [[Alberto Giacometti]], [[Piero Manzoni]], [[Fausto Melotti]], [[Mario Merz]], Maurizio Mochetti, [[Luigi Ontani]], [[Mimmo Paladino]], [[Giulio Paolini]], Claudio Parmiggiani, [[Pino Pascali]], Luca Patella, [[Giuseppe Penone]], Attilio Pierelli, [[Vettor Pisani]], [[Michelangelo Pistolet